From: Raspberry Pi Ltd <kernel@raspberrypi.com>
Date: Mon, 10 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] net: cadence: macb: enable EEE for Raspberry Pi RP1

commit 92ba3307431a upstream

Set MACB_CAPS_EEE for the Raspberry Pi 5 RP1 southbridge
(Cadence GEM_GXL rev 0x00070109 paired with BCM54213PE PHY).
This activates the EEE TX LPI machinery added in the preceding patch
for the RP1 GEM instance.

Backported from rpi-6.18.y kernel (raspberrypi/linux PR #7270).

Link: https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux/commit/3a0bcc7d7a1f
Signed-off-by: Raspberry Pi Ltd <kernel@raspberrypi.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/cadence/macb_main.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/cadence/macb_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/cadence/macb_main.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/cadence/macb_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/cadence/macb_main.c
@@ -5626,7 +5626,8 @@ static const struct macb_config versal_config = {
 static const struct macb_config raspberrypi_rp1_config = {
 	.caps = MACB_CAPS_GIGABIT_MODE_AVAILABLE | MACB_CAPS_CLK_HW_CHG |
 		MACB_CAPS_JUMBO |
-		MACB_CAPS_GEM_HAS_PTP,
+		MACB_CAPS_GEM_HAS_PTP |
+		MACB_CAPS_EEE,
 	.dma_burst_length = 16,
 	.clk_init = macb_clk_init,
 	.init = macb_init,
